The mpd.conf file configures the mpd service to play music in the Raspberry Pi
All files are moved to /home/javier/.mpd folder and the user running mpd is 
changed to "javier", The service is automatilly started at boot time if the 
following command is issued:

sudo update-rc.d mpd enable

The music folder is pointing to /mnt/synology_music, which is mounted when acceded
by the autofs utility.


